The paper discusses the use of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) for prediction tasks, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses active learning, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of GNNs and active learning for graph data also falls under the subfield of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions text and image data, which are subfields of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Computer Vision (cs.CV), respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.SI, cs.CL, and cs.CV.
